 Until meetings are resumed, community members can reach the Nelspruit CPF on mbombelacpf@gmail.com and the Nelspruit CPF Facebook page. “This year will be kicked off with a ‘Safety starts at home’ project, managed by CPF secretary Bianca Wheeler and Callum Mac Pherson, representing one of Mbombela’s security companies at the CPF. “Being involved within your local community is very important, as the project name states, it starts at home,” said CPF chairperson, John Meintjies. “We invite all local subforums or any interested parties to join our monthly meetings, to help make our communities safer.” ALSO READ: Parts of Busamed Lowveld Private Hospital close due to corona scare